{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7faf3cf6-cfb5-4dc3-bd0b-f5f708a110a0","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 — here's the modern approach:\n\n**Constructor injection** is the recommended way to get `TestContext` (MSTest v3+):\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // TestContext injected via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // synchronous init logic here\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test setup\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        await SomeAsyncInitializationAsync();\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test teardown\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        await SomeAsyncCleanupAsync();\n    }\n\n    // One-time async class-level setup\n    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static async Task ClassSetup(TestContext context)\n    {\n        await OneTimeSetupAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Logging from test\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** → synchronous per-test init + `TestContext` injection\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** → async per-test init (supports `Task` return)\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** → async one-time class init (also supports `Task`)\n- Avoid the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern — constructor injection is cleaner and makes the dependency explicit","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dc73e04a-ec88-487c-83cd-e45146330d7c","outputTokens":389,"requestId":"1BC6:1837D6:4E6239:59ADE6:6A03D794"},"id":"344ba95b-496a-494e-a480-a126d1c60abf","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:45:01.333Z","parentId":"5748195a-d1ea-4d1b-b330-51b148d58e49"}
